apsysFW.name: apsysFW
apsysFW.description: Main firmware version. Format: <code version>H<hardware version>D<date>.

apsysBaseId.name: apsysBaseId
apsysBaseId.description: Cluster that the AP belongs to. All APs and SUs in the same cluster shall have the same Base ID.

apsysAPId.name: apsysAPId
apsysAPId.description: AP ID. Each AP in a cluster shall have unique AP ID.

apsysDefOpMode.name: apsysDefOpMode
apsysDefOpMode.description: The operation mode (ap or off) the radio is on after reboot/power cycle.

apsysActivateOpmode.name: apsysActivateOpmode
apsysActivateOpmode.description: Engage AP unit to ap operation mode.

apsysReadCommStr.name: apsysReadCommStr
apsysReadCommStr.description: SNMP agent read community string. It is used for authentication purpose.

apsysWriteCommStr.name: apsysWriteCommStr
apsysWriteCommStr.description: SNMP agent write community string. It is used for authentication purpose.

apsysBlockBroadcastMulticast.name: apsysBlockBroadcastMulticast
apsysBlockBroadcastMulticast.description: This switch enables or disables the blocking of Ethernet control packet except ICMP and ARP to reduce the amount of uneccessary overhead introduced to the wireless link.

apsysSUtoSU.name: apsysSUtoSU
apsysSUtoSU.description: This switch enables or disables the peer-to-peer feature among SUs through the AP. Before this switch is turned on, all SUs that want to communicate with each other have to be assigned to the same group.

apsysTFTPD.name: apsysTFTPD
apsysTFTPD.description: This switch enables or disables the TFTP operation. When it is turned on, then the AP will be ready for code download.

apsysHTTPD.name: apsysHTTPD
apsysHTTPD.description: When it is turned on, then the AP is accessible for configuring via web browser (e.g. IE or Nescape).

apsysMIRThreshold.name: apsysMIRThreshold
apsysMIRThreshold.description: Maximum Information Rate (in Kbps), the AP allows the network to utilize before enforcing CIR on each subscriber.

apsysEthRxAvgThroughputLog.name: apsysEthRxAvgThroughputLog
apsysEthRxAvgThroughputLog.description: Average payload data throughput (in Kbits/sec) received on Ethernet port over the last 60 seconds.

apsysEthTxAvgThroughputLog.name: apsysEthTxAvgThroughputLog
apsysEthTxAvgThroughputLog.description: Average payload data throughput (in Kbits/sec) transmitted on Ethernet port over the last 60 seconds.

apsysRfRxAvgThroughputLog.name: apsysRfRxAvgThroughputLog
apsysRfRxAvgThroughputLog.description: Average payload data throughput (in Kbits/sec) received on RF port over the last 60 seconds.

apsysRfTxAvgThroughputLog.name: apsysRfTxAvgThroughputLog
apsysRfTxAvgThroughputLog.description: Average payload data throughput (in Kbits/sec) transmitted on RF port over the last 60 seconds.

apsysEthInOctets.name: apsysEthInOctets
apsysEthInOctets.description: Number of payload octets received on Ethernet port.

apsysEthOutOctets.name: apsysEthOutOctets
apsysEthOutOctets.description: Number of payload octets transmitted on Ethernet port.

apsysRfInOctets.name: apsysRfInOctets
apsysRfInOctets.description: Number of octets of SUs payload received from RF port.

apsysRfOutOctets.name: apsysRfOutOctets
apsysRfOutOctets.description: Number of octets of SUs payload transmitted to RF port.

apsysUpdateFlashAndActivate.name: apsysUpdateFlashAndActivate
apsysUpdateFlashAndActivate.description: Save system setting values to Flash and activate the settings.

aprfActiveChannel.name: aprfActiveChannel
aprfActiveChannel.description: It specifies the current channel number the radio operates on.

aprfActivePolarization.name: aprfActivePolarization
aprfActivePolarization.description: It specifies the current polarization the radio operates on.

aprfChannel1.description: RF channel 1 frequency (in MHz). It allows you to create your own channel instead of the manufacturing defaults in the AP. Keep in mind that channel width is 20MHz, and the frequency specified here is the center frequency. Frequency (5260MHz - 5340MHz) is only applicable to M5830S radio.

aprfismTxPowerMax.name: aprfismTxPowerMax
aprfismTxPowerMax.description: The maximum ISM Tx power value can be set (in dBm).

aprfismTxPowerMin.name: aprfismTxPowerMin
aprfismTxPowerMin.description: The minimum ISM Tx power value can be set (in dBm).

aprfismTxPower.name: aprfismTxPower
aprfismTxPower.description: ISM RF tx power (in dBm). It specifies the power output of the radio, excluding the antenna gain. Check parameters aprfismTxPowerMax and aprfismTxPowerMin for power setting range.

aprfismServiceRadius.name: aprfismServiceRadius
aprfismServiceRadius.description: ISM RF service radius (in mile). It specifies the distance of the furthest SU the AP will serve. Based on this information, the AP will determine the maximum wait time for a SU to response to a poll before it starts to poll the next one.

aprfismRxThreshold.name: aprfismRxThreshold
aprfismRxThreshold.description: ISM RF rx threshold (in dBm). It specifies the receiver sensitivity of the AP. By default, the radio's sensitivity is -82dBm. The higher the threshold is, the less sensitive the radio will be. In M5800S, the value -90 represents the rfrxthreshold is disabled.

aprfismTargetRSSI.name: aprfismTargetRSSI
aprfismTargetRSSI.description: ISM RF target RSSI (in dBm). It specifies the target RSSI from all SUs to the AP. Based on this parameter, the AP can power level each SU so that it receives same level of signal strength from all SUs, regardless far or near. Note that when you set the Target RSSI from SU, you need to consider AP's RF Rx Threshold value. The Target RSSI from SU must be 5dB higher than the RF Rx Threshold. When the RF Rx Threshold is disabled, the setting of the Target RSSI from SU shall be no less than -75dBm.

aprfuniiTxPowerMax.name: aprfuniiTxPowerMax
aprfuniiTxPowerMax.description: This object is only applicable to M5830S radio. The maximum UNII Tx power value can be set (in dBm).

aprfuniiTxPowerMin.name: aprfuniiTxPowerMin
aprfuniiTxPowerMin.description: This object is only applicable to M5830S radio. The minimum UNII Tx power value can be set (in dBm).

aprfuniiTxPower.name: aprfuniiTxPower
aprfuniiTxPower.description: This object is only applicable to M5830S radio. UNII RF tx power (in dBm). It specifies the power output of the radio, excluding the antenna gain. Check parameters aprfuniiTxPowerMax and aprfuniiTxPowerMin for power setting range.

aprfuniiServiceRadius.name: aprfuniiServiceRadius
aprfuniiServiceRadius.description: This object is only applicable to M5830S radio. UNII RF service radius (in mile). It specifies the distance of the furthest SU the AP will serve. Based on this information, the AP will determine the maximum wait time for a SU to response to a poll before it starts to poll the next one.

aprfuniiRxThreshold.name: aprfuniiRxThreshold
aprfuniiRxThreshold.description: This object is only applicable to M5830S radio. UNII RF rx threshold (in dBm). It specifies the receiver sensitivity of the AP.

aprfuniiTargetRSSI.name: aprfuniiTargetRSSI
aprfuniiTargetRSSI.description: This object is only applicable to M5830S radio. UNII RF target RSSI (in dBm). It specifies the target RSSI from all SUs to the AP. Based on this parameter, the AP can power level each SU so that it receives same level of signal strength from all SUs, regardless far or near. Note that when you set the Target RSSI from SU, you need to consider AP's RF Rx Threshold value. The Target RSSI from SU must be 5dB higher than the RF Rx Threshold.

suSUCount.name: suSUCount
suSUCount.description: Number of subscriber units in the subscriber database.

suPowerLvlAll.name: suPowerLvlAll
suPowerLvlAll.description: It is a feature that is typically found in more elaborate mobile systems such as cellular CDMA networks. Using this feature, all SUs have their RF power output adjusted until the signal strength for each SU as received in the AP is roughly the same.

suStatisticsSamplePeriod.name: suStatisticsSamplePeriod
suStatisticsSamplePeriod.description: A period (in minute) AP requests update on SU Info Table from all associated SUs.

suRebootAll.name: suRebootAll
suRebootAll.description: AP broadcasts reboot command to all subscriber units.

suAddOrDeleteID.name: suAddOrDeleteID
suAddOrDeleteID.description: Subscriber unit ID (1..8190). Each subscriber in a sector shall have a unique ID.

suAddMAC.name: suAddMAC
suAddMAC.description: It is the MAC address of the subscriber unit, which can be found on the back of the SU.

suAddPolling.name: suAddPolling
suAddPolling.description: It is service level value, regular or priority, of a SU. The AP will poll priority user more often, thus better network latency as the result. As the network latency varies based on the number of subscriber units the AP serves, priority user is guaranteed that the latency is NOT greater than 100ms regardless of the size of the network.

suAddSUtoSU.name: suAddSUtoSU
suAddSUtoSU.description: It is peer-to-peer group this SU belongs to. With the SU to SU switch is turned on, SUs in the same peer-to-peer group can communicate to each other via the AP. There are totally 15 groups available. Note that the SU shall be set to priority user for this feature to improve latency.

suAddCIR.name: suAddCIR
suAddCIR.description: It is the Committed Information Rate (in Kbps) the AP allocates to SU.

suAddMIR.name: suAddMIR
suAddMIR.description: It is the Maximum Information Rate (in Kbps) the AP allocates to SU.

suAdd.name: suAdd
suAdd.description: Add a subscriber (specified in object suAddOrDeleteID) to the subscriber database.

suDelete.name: suDelete
suDelete.description: Delete a subscriber (specified in object suAddOrDeleteID) from the subscriber database.

suInfoTable.name: suInfoTable
suInfoTable.description: A table that contains subscriber unit entities.

suInfoEntry.name: suInfoEntry
suInfoEntry.description: Information about a specific subscriber unit retrieved by its ID number.

suID.name: suID
suID.description: Subscriber unit ID. Each subscriber in a sector shall have a unique ID.

suMAC.name: suMAC
suMAC.description: Subscriber unit MAC Address. Format: 00 01 DE xx xx xx.

suPolling.name: suPolling
suPolling.description: It is service level value, regular or priority, of a SU. The AP will poll priority user more often, thus better network latency as the result. As the network latency varies based on the number of subscriber units the AP serves, priority user is guaranteed that the latency is NOT greater than 100ms regardless of the size of the network.

suSUtoSU.name: suSUtoSU
suSUtoSU.description: It is peer-to-peer group this SU belongs to. With the SU to SU switch is turned on, SUs in the same peer-to-peer group can communicate to each other via the AP. There are totally 15 groups available. Note that the SU shall be set to priority user for this feature to improve latency.

suCIR.name: suCIR
suCIR.description: It is the Committed Information Rate (in Kbps) the AP allocates to SU.

suMIR.name: suMIR
suMIR.description: It is the Maximum Information Rate (in Kbps) the AP allocates to SU.

suRSSIFromSU.name: suRSSIFromSU
suRSSIFromSU.description: Subscriber unit RSSI from SU (in dBm).

suRSSIFromAP.name: suRSSIFromAP
suRSSIFromAP.description: Subscriber unit RSSI from AP (in dBm).

suTxPower.name: suTxPower
suTxPower.description: Subscriber unit Tx Power Level (in dBm).

suEthRxAvgThroughputLog.name: suEthRxAvgThroughputLog
suEthRxAvgThroughputLog.description: Average payload data throughput (in Kbits/sec) received on the Ethernet port over the period specified by suStatisticsSamplePeriod.

suEthTxAvgThroughputLog.name: suEthTxAvgThroughputLog
suEthTxAvgThroughputLog.description: Average payload data throughput (in Kbits/sec) transmitted on the Ethernet port over the period specified by suStatisticsSamplePeriod.

suRfRxAvgThroughputLog.name: suRfRxAvgThroughputLog
suRfRxAvgThroughputLog.description: Average payload data throughput (in Kbits/sec) received on the RF port over the period specified by suStatisticsSamplePeriod.

suRfTxAvgThroughputLog.name: suRfTxAvgThroughputLog
suRfTxAvgThroughputLog.description: Average payload data throughput (in Kbits/sec) transmitted on the RF port over the period specified by suStatisticsSamplePeriod.

suRfInOctets.name: suRfInOctets
suRfInOctets.description: Number of payload octets received on the RF port.

suRfOutOctets.name: suRfOutOctets
suRfOutOctets.description: Number of payload octets transmitted on the RF port.

suPowerLevel.name: suPowerLevel
suPowerLevel.description: It is a feature that is typically found in more elaborate mobile systems such as cellular CDMA networks. Using this feature, the SU has its RF power output adjusted until its signal strength received in the AP is roughly the same.

suTemperature.name: suTemperature
suTemperature.description: Subscriber Unit temperature reading value (in Celsius).

suReboot.name: suReboot
suReboot.description: AP issues reboot command to a specific subscriber unit.

aptrpTable.name: aptrpTable
aptrpTable.description: A table that contains information of Trango trap events .

aptrpEntry.name: aptrpEntry
aptrpEntry.description: Information about a specific Trango trap event.

aptrpEnable.name: aptrpEnable
aptrpEnable.description: Enable a specific Trango trap event or not.

suLinkUp.name: suLinkUp
suLinkUp.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when a specific SU Associated.

suLinkDown.name: suLinkDown
suLinkDown.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when a specific SU Powered Off.

apOpModeFailure.name: apOpModeFailure
apOpModeFailure.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when a specific AP not being in ap mode during boot up sequence.
